705268f-a.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Clarendon Road
705268f-a.text:
Eings Highway, south from Clarendon Road, showing the Cornelius Eouwenhoven house on the left, on the N.E. corner of Kings Highway and
Ave. D.
.September 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
The same, showing a closer view of the house.
June 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

705269f-a.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Clarendon Road
705269f-a.text:
Kings Highway, at the S.E. corner of Clarendon Road, just south of Canarsie Lane, showing the J. C. Vanderveer House, owned by the C. Vanderveer Estate in 1860. John Vanderveer operated a grooery here about 1864. In 1900 it was Will Mathews house. It was partly
burned about 1921, and demolished in May 1925.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
The same, from another angle.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
